You invoke the method `getOrder` internally from the same bean. This means that the call would not be able to take into consideration the annotation `@PostAuthorize` when invoked internally, since the call will be made by the actual class that this method belongs to and not by the spring proxy class which will contain the actual code for the functionality of `PostAuthorize`.

